KANO – Malam Ibrahim Shekarau, senator representing Kano Central, at the red chamber of the National Assembly, on Sunday announced that he has secured four new power stations for Kano under the constituency projects. Shekarau, who hosted media men to a luncheon on Sunday in Kano disclosed that the new stations would be cited at Gezawa, Modobi, Nasarawa, and Tarauni local areas of the state. The two-term former Kano State governor revealed that the projects were captured in 2021 Appropriation Bill that was assented to by Mr President a couple of days ago. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Shekarau explained that he has set up a Technical Committee on behalf of Kano Central Senatorial District to liaise with relevant stakeholders to ensure all projects already captured under the constituency project are attended to. Details soon…. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION